deck: Zeron, space warrior, is found by two college girls who are telepathically linked to him, and he tries to assimilate to a world that is alien to him. But there are hidden enemies who want revenge.
description: When Spring break came for college students Ashley Montgomery and Kirby Katzenberg, little did they know that they would stumble onto a close encounter to change their lives. Alien Warrior Doktralian Zeron has returned to the world of his ancestors as a decommissioned, Galactic veteran, heralding the homecoming of his race. They hope for a quiet assimilation, yet there are those who want the mission to fail. Many generations have passed, living and dying on alien landscapes, but with the war won, their dream is to return home. But there are those who wish to exact revenge on the Drunan (Human-alien hybrid), and they want an end to the one race that could oppose a ressurection...
name: Zeron

Carrying on the tradition of the previous title, Classic Judge Dredd reprinted the lawman's adventures from 2000AD in printing order.

To coincide with the release of the 1995 Judge Dredd movie, the series was restarted from issue 1 and retitled Classic Judge Dredd (and became a companion title for the also recently relaunched Classic 2000AD).

Classic Judge Dredd lasted 18 issues and carried on reprinting Dredd's adventures from prog 424 up to the end of the Oz saga (prog 570).

description:
This is a CHEW spin off one-shot created by Writer John Layman and Artist Rob Guillory to shed some more light on Poyo, one of the most mysterious characters in the series. Though this was just a one shot story, Layman hinted towards the end that there could be a possibility of a sequel in the future. However, it could just be for comedic relief when it was planted in this comic.

This story follows Poyo and Agent Barnes stopping the mad scientist, Regenbogen, from making the skies rain; Animals! This one-shot also features pin-up artwork of Poyo.
name: Chew: Secret Agent Poyo

description:
Volume 3

A Valiant ongoing series starring the title character Bloodshot.

Your name is Angelo Mortalli. Your brother is trapped behind enemy lines and on the verge of — no. That’s not right. Your name is Raymond Garrison. You’ve retired from the dangers of the field, but a desperate plea from your oldest friend plunges you into a vicious firefight that — no. That’s not right, either. You are Bloodshot. You are the shade of gray that freedom requires. The perfect confluence of military necessity and cutting-edge technology. A walking WikiLeaks. A reservoir of dirty secrets that could set the world on fire. And you’ve just been captured.

With issue #14 the title changes to Bloodshot and H.A.R.D. Corps and then changes back to Bloodshot with issue #24.

Written by Duane Swierczynski (#1-13) and Matt Kindt (#0).

Art by:

  • Manuel Garcia and Arturo Lozzi (#1-6, #8)
  • Matthew Clark (#7)
  • Manuel Garcia (#9)
  • Barry Kitson (#10-13)
  • ChrisCross (#0)

Translated into Spanish.

Collected Editions

  • Bloodshot Deluxe Edition Book Two (#24-25 & 0)
